thing's getting me feeling my age.

282
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:09,314
What are you talking about?
Would you stop that?

283
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:11,277
Sam Malone never ages.

284
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:13,271
It's one of life's great truths.

285
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:15,396
Let me tell you something,
Sammy.

286
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:18,632
When you're 87,
you'll still be a hunk to me.

287
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,070
Of course, I'll be senile and blind.

288
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:27,079
- And pregnant.
- Yeah, probably.

289
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:31,073
- I'll look you up.
- You better.

290
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:35,831
Fun's over.
See you around, Sam.

291
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,752
Thank you, Carla.

292
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:38,955
Bye, Carla.

293
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:42,510
You see? There are other parts to a
hospital besides the maternity ward.

294
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:44,113
Bite it.

295
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:47,797
Hi, Sam. How are you?

296
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:51,111
I don't even know why you bother
asking. You know how I am. I'm old.

297
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:53,999
- Sam, please.
- No, no, no, you were right.

298
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:58,195
You know, I tried denying it,
but it's no use.

299
00:17:58,360 --> 00:18:03,150
