is slowing down, wearing out,

300
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:04,992
and breaking the occasional hip.

301
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:07,230
Oh, Sam!

302
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:11,597
Oh, I can't stand to hear you
talk like that. You were right.

303
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:15,435
I was wrong. You can't just lie back
and accept getting old.

304
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:18,319
You have to live each day
to the fullest.

305
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:23,596
I don't know. It's...

306
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:27,750
No, really, I mean it.

307
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:32,675
Besides, you men get better looking
the older that you get.

308
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:34,796
Look at this guy.

309
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,632
Huh?

310
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,199
Strong.

311
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:39,759
Vital.

312
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,273
Sexy.

313
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:43,476
Isn't he something?

314
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:48,638
You really think
I'm better looking now?

315
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:52,874
You're a much more attractive man
than when I first met you. Much more.

316
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,912
And there's no telling
what you may yet achieve.

317
00:18:57,080 --> 00:18:59,230
I went to the library today,

318
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:03,632
and I found a book
that contains a list of people

319
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:07,713
